Glossary
Caveolae: protein-driven plasma membrane invaginations (of 60–80 nm diameter) enriched in cholesterol, sphingolipids, and caveolin protein oligomers. Cortical tension: the tension borne by the actin cortex beneath the plasma membrane. In-plane tension: the component of membrane tension due to osmotic pressure differences across the plasma membrane. Membrane–cytoskeleton adhesion: the component of membrane tension due to the multitude of weak binding interactions between cytoskeletal components and membrane phospholipids. Keeps the membrane tightly adhered to the surface of the cytoskeleton. Membrane tension: the apparent tension in the membrane containing contributions from membrane–cytoskeleton adhesion and osmotic pressure.
